						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">From what I can remember including it all at once won't work. NESASM is also really shitty with error messages in situations like this. I believe hearing this &quot;bank crossing&quot; works in zzo38's modified version of NESASM, although I haven't used it myself.</div><br />I'm using a NESASM all the time and I can say with all confidence it does work. Even more-I'm making a MMC3 project right now. The &quot;bank crossing&quot; applies only to code, not data. Getting the right Bank number can be hard if you have a big chr, however, so I would split it.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Question: Under the settings I have, what bank numbers represent which sections of my tiles.chr?</div><br />You start from zero. So if you write 0 to $8001 as your bank number, then the beggining of the chr data will be used and placed into ppu. How many tiles and where exactly depends on $8000 setting.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">For example, how could I take the information at $4000-$43FF of my tiles.chr and bank switch that into the PPU at say, PPU $1000-$13FF?</div><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #%00000010<br />sta $8000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; So our piece of chr will be put into $1000-$13FF in ppu<br /><br />lda #$10<br />sta $8001&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;Take our piece of chr data and put it into ppu.<br /></div></div>

